  "identifier": "ConsTree",
  "description": "Efficient construction of phylogenetic consensus trees from a set of input trees. Methods include strict, majority-rule, majority-rule (+), loose (combinable component / semi-strict), greedy, Adams, frequency difference, R*, and local consensus, computed using asymptotically efficient algorithms. Builds on 'TreeTools' for the manipulation of trees and splits.",
